---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import ResponsiveImage from "../components/ResponsiveImage.astro";
import RouteBoard from "../components/RouteBoard.astro";
---

<SiteLayout title="Our Story · Rangeway" description="Rangeway brings hospitality operating experience and EV-driver perspective to the charging stop." class="story-family">
  <!-- HERO: A road-width thesis interrupts a visual timeline of the company in motion. -->
  <section class="story-photo-masthead">
    <ResponsiveImage class="story-photo-masthead__image" src="/images/hero-mountain-waystation.webp" srcSmall="/images/hero-mountain-waystation-640.webp" alt="Concept rendering of a Rangeway charging lounge and timber canopy at sunset in a mountain landscape" width={1672} height={941} sizes="100vw" loading="eager" position="center 62%" />
    <p class="concept-label concept-label--hero">Concept rendering</p>
    <div class="story-photo-masthead__veil" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="story-photo-masthead__copy">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--sun">Our story / Roadside hospitality</p>
      <h1>Hospitality is how the road gets better.</h1>
      <p>Rangeway is a hospitality company that happens to charge vehicles.</p>
      <blockquote>The point is not to interrupt the journey. It is to make the journey feel cared for.</blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story-origin">
    <p class="story-origin__marker">Origin / Operating point of view</p>
    <div class="story-origin__statement">
      <p>Drivers are guests.</p><p>Stops are experiences.</p><p>The wait is the product.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="story-origin__copy">
      <p>Rangeway was founded from an unusual combination: years spent operating luxury resorts, wellness retreats, and flagship urban hotels, alongside firsthand experience in the EV-driver community.</p>
      <p>The charging industry has largely treated the stop as a utility problem. We see a hospitality problem: light, shelter, clean facilities, calm service, and a place that respects the time between arrival and departure.</p>
      <p>Every Rangeway format is designed as a place a traveler would choose, not merely tolerate. The scale changes with the road. The care does not.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story-beliefs">
    <header><p class="eyebrow">Operating beliefs</p><h2>Four decisions behind every stop.</h2></header>
    <div class="story-beliefs__field">
      <article><span>01</span><h3>Make the wait good.</h3><p>If a driver has to wait, the stop has a responsibility to make that time useful and comfortable.</p></article>
      <article><span>02</span><h3>Operate the details.</h3><p>Lighting, lavatories, provisions, seating, and service are operating decisions, not decorative features.</p></article>
      <article><span>03</span><h3>Plan real corridors.</h3><p>We build around routes people actually drive and the communities those roads connect.</p></article>
      <article><span>04</span><h3>Hold one standard.</h3><p>Waystation, Basecamp, and Summit should feel made by the same company and held to the same promise.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story-current">
    <header><p class="eyebrow eyebrow--sun">Current work</p><h2>The story is being built in public.</h2><p>Rangeway is developing projects, building partnerships, publishing Field Notes, raising capital, and hiring. The first locations remain in development.</p></header>
    <RouteBoard title="Three regions. One operating standard." intro="Follow the public project surfaces for sourced updates from Bozeman, Mojave / Antelope Valley, and St. Louis." />
  </section>

  <section class="story-team-handoff">
    <p class="eyebrow">The people</p>
    <h2>Different disciplines.<br />One guest standard.</h2>
    <div><p>Hospitality operations, design and construction, growth, policy, and public capital come together around a simple brief: make the stop better.</p><a class="button button--sun" href="/team">Meet the team</a></div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .story-photo-masthead { position: relative; min-height: min(1000px,100svh); background: var(--navy-deep); color: white; overflow: hidden; }
  .story-photo-masthead__image, .story-photo-masthead__veil { position: absolute; inset: 0; }
  .story-photo-masthead__veil { background: linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(9,26,32,.16) 18%,rgba(9,26,32,.88) 94%), linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(9,26,32,.58),transparent 72%); }
  .story-photo-masthead__copy { position: relative; z-index: 1; display: flex; min-height: inherit; flex-direction: column; justify-content: flex-end; padding: 190px var(--page-pad) 68px; }
  .story-photo-masthead h1 { max-width: 11ch; margin: 0 0 26px; font-size: clamp(4.5rem,9.2vw,9.8rem); }
  .story-photo-masthead__copy > p:not(.eyebrow) { max-width: 38ch; margin: 0; color: rgba(255,255,255,.76); font-size: 1.12rem; }
  .story-photo-masthead blockquote { align-self: flex-end; width: min(520px,46vw); margin: -30px 0 0; padding: 24px 0 0; border-top: 3px solid var(--sun); font: 700 clamp(1.35rem,2.4vw,2.5rem)/1.08 var(--font-display); letter-spacing: -.04em; }
  .story-origin { display: grid; grid-template-columns: .5fr 1.1fr .8fr; gap: clamp(30px,5vw,90px); padding: var(--section-pad) var(--page-pad); background: var(--cream); }
  .story-origin__marker { color: var(--oxide); font: 600 .65rem var(--font-mono); letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .story-origin__statement p { margin: 0; font: 700 clamp(2.7rem,5vw,5.8rem)/.92 var(--font-display); letter-spacing: -.06em; }
  .story-origin__statement p:nth-child(2) { color: var(--oxide); }
  .story-origin__copy { padding-top: 12px; color: var(--slate); }
  .story-beliefs { padding: var(--section-pad) var(--page-pad); background: var(--warm-white); }
  .story-beliefs > header { display: grid; grid-template-columns: .55fr 1.45fr; max-width: 1440px; margin: 0 auto 70px; }
  .story-beliefs h2 { max-width: 10ch; font-size: clamp(3.5rem,7vw,7.3rem); }
  .story-beliefs__field { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(12,1fr); gap: 18px; max-width: 1440px; margin: auto; }
  .story-beliefs article { grid-column: span 3; min-height: 370px; padding: 26px; border-top: 5px solid var(--sun); background: var(--navy); color: white; }
  .story-beliefs article:nth-child(even) { transform: translateY(48px); background: var(--cream); color: var(--navy-deep); }
  .story-beliefs article span { font: 500 .7rem var(--font-mono); color: var(--oxide); }
  .story-beliefs article h3 { margin: 120px 0 18px; font-size: 2rem; }
  .story-beliefs article p { color: inherit; opacity: .7; font-size: .92rem; }
  .story-current { padding-top: var(--section-pad); background: var(--navy-deep); color: white; }
  .story-current > header { display: grid; grid-template-columns: .45fr 1fr .7fr; gap: 40px; align-items: end; padding: 0 var(--page-pad) 38px; }
  .story-current h2 { margin: 0; font-size: clamp(3rem,5vw,5.8rem); }
  .story-current header > p:last-child { color: rgba(255,255,255,.68); }
  .story-current :global(.route-board) { padding-top: 70px; }
  .story-team-handoff { display: grid; grid-template-columns: .35fr 1.1fr .55fr; gap: 38px; align-items: end; padding: var(--section-pad) var(--page-pad); background: var(--oxide); color: white; }
  .story-team-handoff h2 { margin: 0; font-size: clamp(3.4rem,6.7vw,7rem); }
  .story-team-handoff > div p { color: rgba(255,255,255,.78); }
  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .story-photo-masthead { min-height: 820px; }
    .story-photo-masthead__copy { padding: 140px 20px 46px; }
    .story-photo-masthead blockquote { align-self: flex-start; width: 100%; margin-top: 42px; }
    .story-origin, .story-current > header, .story-team-handoff { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding-inline: 20px; }
    .story-beliefs { padding-inline: 20px; }
    .story-beliefs > header { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .story-beliefs__field { display: block; }
    .story-beliefs article { min-height: 300px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .story-beliefs article:nth-child(even) { transform: none; }
  }
</style>
